48. Adjustments. When an adjustment event occurs‚ a taxpayer may, at such
amount‚ on such terms‚ within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, claim
adjustments in the following cases‚ namely:—
(a) an increasing or decreasing adjustment with respect to withholding
tax;
(b) an increasing or decreasing adjustment applicable in consequence of
an annual re- assessment;
(c) an increasing adjustment for not making payments through banking
channels;
(d) an increasing adjustment for goods put to a private use;
(e) an increasing adjustment of input tax and VAT on being registered;
(f) an increasing adjustment on cancellation of registration;
